This paper deals with regularity of functions that map input strings to a monoid, which is a topic in formal language theory (cs.FL). It also involves the use of finite-state transducers and automata, which are common tools in data structures (cs.DS) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses regular expressions, which are a fundamental concept in computational linguistics (cs.CL). Finally, the paper mentions document processing, which is a topic in databases (cs.DB).
